The paper discusses deep neural networks and their application in semi-supervised learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses experiments involving image classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the sensitivity of SSL methods to the amount of labeled and unlabeled data, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of SSL in natural language processing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of SSL methods in real-world applications, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
